OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1779847405
OL,3,CFour-fifths of UK firms impacted by
OL,4,CIran war fallout ` report
OL,6,FAnalysis of Barclays data from around
OL,7,F900,000 businesses showed small
OL,8,Fcompanies in particular are taking
OL,9,Faction in the face of uncertainty and
OL,10,Fcost pressures, with a 13.1% drop in
OL,11,Fborrowing during the first three
OL,12,Fmonths of 2026 and 1.5% increase in
OL,13,Fsavings as they look to build up a
OL,14,Fbuffer.
OL,16,FThe report showed that larger firms
OL,17,Fare still focusing on longer-term
OL,18,Finvestment, with a 6.9% increase in
OL,19,Flonger-term borrowing and 5.2% drop in
OL,20,Fsavings.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1779847405
OL,3,CFour-fifths of UK firms impacted by
OL,4,CIran war fallout ` report
OL,6,FBut 20% of companies overall are
OL,7,Fpausing investment against a backdrop
OL,8,Fof geopolitical uncertainty in a sign
OL,9,Fof the impact of the war on the UK
OL,10,Feconomy.
OL,12,FMatt Hammerstein, chief executive of
OL,13,FBarclays UK Corporate Bank, said: "UK
OL,14,Fbusinesses are now operating in an
OL,15,Fenvironment where uncertainty has
OL,16,Fbecome the norm.
OL,18,F"Geopolitical instability and
OL,19,Fpersistently high costs are feeding
OL,20,Fdirectly into cashflows, borrowing
OL,21,Fdecisions and investment plans."
OL,26,@uD@cOUzD@AOU}D@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1779847405
OL,3,CFour-fifths of UK firms impacted by
OL,4,CIran war fallout ` report
OL,6,FBut the data suggests larger
OL,7,Fcorporates are doubling down on their
OL,8,Fspending on technology, in particular
OL,9,Fartificial intelligence (AI) and
OL,10,Fcybersecurity.
OL,12,FNearly seven in 10 (68%) firms are
OL,13,Fplanning to increase their
OL,14,Fcybersecurity investment over the next
OL,15,Fyear, while recent spending on AI has
OL,16,Fseen more than half (61%) now claim to
OL,17,Fbe using agentic AI in their
OL,18,Foperations.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
